      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACK KERMARO (8) goes very well at the course and distance with five wins and a placing from nine starts. Below best last time at this track (17.89) in a Grade 5, finishing a 5 length sixth. Has the ability and should feature. REMA'S MARBLE (1) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing sixth (19.00) in a Grade 5 at Richmond. Solid record at the distance winning six races. Should play a prominent role. TARAWI TANK (5) dropped out early but wound up strongly and charged into the minors when a 1.3 lengths third (17.87) at this track in Grade 5. Rarely misses off this draw. Has a solid record from this box including three wins and a minor placing. Must be included in calculations. DESPICABLE MILO (2) placed last start and is in the mix again.",
